Colonial Secretary's Office
Sierra Leone 31st Jany 1874

Sir,

In reply to your letter of the 22nd instant, relative to the detention by Mr.Hard of Leone upon archives for rent, I am directed by His Excellency the Governor-in-Chief to inform you that the proper <unclear/> would be for you to apply to the legal tribunal of this settlement , for the purpose of determining the question whether or not <unclear/> Harris His agent was justified in <unclear/> the consular property referred to, for their rent, as this is a legal question, which the Judge, and not His Excellency is to decide.

His Excellency therefore cannot interfere with M<unclear/> Harris His agent under the circumstances <unclear/> in his assertion of a legal right.

I have the honor to be
Sir
Your most obdt Servant
John Ashwood
Acting Colonial Secr

M.Ryons Esq

